channel.title: I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library
channel.description:
A week ago I looked for the original post boasting the blistering speed at which ppsuqbawlz's bytecode library was both written and functions, it would seem that it has been deleted, needless to say I was heart broken.
This post is meant to be all in good fun!
I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library with all of his fingers broken. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library in binary. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library using a [url=http://unix.rulez.org/~calver/pictures/supercoder.jpg]supercoder keyboard[/url] with half of the keys missing. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library on an abacus. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library in the amount of time it took to submit this topic. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library while itching his cisterna magna cerebellomedularis. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library using an industrial sized magnet on his tower. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library while his power cable was unplugged. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library faster than Chuck Norris would round house kick you in the face. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library with two broken arms and no monitor. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library with On Screen Keyboard with a broken mouse. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library in 30 minutes just using his nose. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library while splitting an atom with his eyelashes. I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library with using Microsoft's speech recognition, without a microphone.
If you have your own you would like added, just post them, if they are deemed appropriate I will add them to the list
okay, incase you havent caught on, you are meant to finish the sentence "I heard that pplsuqbawlz programmed his bytecode library..." with some outlandish claim, similar to those of chuck norris or the stig
